  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\"><div class=\"fr-view\"><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><strong>Week 1 Overview</strong></span></p></div><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>You will learn the basic of self-introduction, the polite form of verbs and all hiragana (46 characters).</span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><strong><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Day 1&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p><ol start=\"1\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;\" type=\"1\"><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on the particles ha and mo (は, も)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Particle ka to express questions and doubts (か)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Counting from 1 to 100&nbsp;</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>10 hiragana (あ, い, う, え, お, か, き, く, け, こ)</span></span></li></ol><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><strong><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Day 2</span></strong></span></p><ol start=\"1\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;\" type=\"1\"><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on kono, sono, ano (この, その, あの)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on nan and dare (なん, だれ)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on no (の) to indicate possession</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Counting from 101 to 1000</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>10 hiragana (さ</span><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>,&nbsp;</span><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>し, す, せ, そ, た, ち, つ, て, と)</span></span></li></ol><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><strong><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Day 3</span></strong></span></p><ol start=\"1\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;\" type=\"1\"><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on koko, soko, asoko (ここ, そこ</span><span style='font-family:\"Microsoft Yi Baiti\";'>、</span><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>あそこ)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on no (の) to categorize something&nbsp;</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on doko, ikura (どこ, いくら)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Counting up to 100,000, counting yen, things, and floors</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>10 hiragana (な, に, ぬ, ね, の, は, ひ, ふ, へ, ほ)</span></span></li></ol><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><strong><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Day 4&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p><ol start=\"1\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;\" type=\"1\"><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on the particle wo (を), present tense (V-masu) and negative form (V-masen)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on the particle de (で) and to (と)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on nani (なに)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Expressing time (today, tomorrow, yesterday, etc.)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>8 hiragana (ま, み, む, め, も, や, ゆ, よ)</span></span></li></ol><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><strong><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Day 5&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p><ol start=\"1\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;\" type=\"1\"><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>How to tell time (What time is it?)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on the particles ni, kara, made, goro (に, から, まで, ごろ)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>Grammar focus on past tense (V-mashita)</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;color:#5B5B5B;background:white;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\",\"serif\";'>8 hiragana (ら, り, る, れ, ろ, わ, を, ん)</span></span></li></ol><div class=\"fr-view\"><p><br></p></div></div>",
